    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-03T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-03T15:00:00-05:00" n="502"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2754: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d502fn1">See last paragraph for instructions to
                        repeat to Paris as no. 677.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-03T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 3, 1920—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>344. The following is a copy of a memorandum handed to the Department today by
                    Ambassador Shidehara the paragraphs of which are lettered for purposes of
                    eventual comment:</p>
                <p>[Here follows the memorandum of April 3 from the Japanese Embassy, printed <hi
                        rend="italic">supra.</hi>]</p>
                <p>Please communicate the above to the Foreign Office for its information with the
                    statement that this Government is giving the memorandum consideration and will
                    communicate its opinion in the course of a few days and ask that in the meantime
                    the British Government-withhold any further communication on the subject to the
                    Japanese Government as referred to in your 545, April 1, 7 p.m.</p>
                <p>Repeat to Paris as number 677.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
